stylometry: For our project we did a @risksimtable. We did this type of model because we wanted to forecast a simulation of how many games Madden 2012 would sell this upcoming fall. We researched what the developer costs, unit price, and advertising caosts were for madden 2011. By using this data we found out how much it would be to make and market the game. We then used triangular distribution to find the max., min, and most likely people that would buy the game and for them to still make a profit. I learned a lot from this. The @risk model showed me that even by not knowing how many you will sell it can still show you the right amount you would need to sell to make a profit by using the data from the simulation.
